<h2 id="lessons" class="font-semibold text-xl mb-2 mt-4">Lessons Learned</h2>
<ol class="list-decimal list-inside mt-2">
  <li>Too much playtesting can take away from development efforts</li>
  <li>It is important to develop specific questions to ask playtesters.</li>
  <li>Very good qualitative data was impartitive to improving our design.</li>
</ol>

<h3 id="learned" class="font-semibold mt-4">How We Learned This</h3>
<h4>Lesson 1</h4>
  <p class="ml-8">We underestimated the impact that 2 hours of playtesting meant in the time span of the one term MQP. This meant that playtesting cut into a more significant portion of development time than expected.</p>
<h4>Lesson 2</h4>
  <p class="ml-8">We found this as playtesters themselves often had trouble qualitatively assessing certain aspects that were more subtle.</p>
<h4>Lesson 3</h4>
  <p class="ml-8"> We found that as a platformer it is hard to understand what to change merely through numerical values.</p>

